title: Independent candidate Naseem Ali Shah wins NA-39
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Abdul Latif won the National Assembly constituency NA-39, Bannu election by securing 147,087 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Zahid Akram Durrani Jamiat Ulma-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI) Candidate, who bagged 110,675 votes.
Votersâ€™ turn-out remained at 39.43 per cent.
